                    "measure": "Gastrointestinal (GI) total symptoms score (TSS)",
                    "description": "The primary outcome measures are patient symptoms via the traditional gastroparesis patient reported outcome scale. It uses a 0-4 scale from none to worse on GI Symptoms; for example: Nausea,Vomiting, Anorexia/Early Satiety, Bloating/distension, Abdominal Pain. Scored as each item plus a total that is the sum of the individual scales.The five Sx subscales of 0-4 each are summed for a total score range 0-20",
